            <h2>Privacy Policy Statement</h2>
            <p>1. The Travel Industry Authority (TIA) is:<br>
            <p>   (a) dedicated to the protection of personal data privacy; and<br>
                  (b) committed to compliance with the Personal Data (Privacy) Ordinance (Cap. 486) (PDPO), in particular the Data Protection Principles as stated in Schedule 1 thereto.<br>
         
            <h3>Personal Data Collected</h3>
    
            <p>2. In performing its statutory functions, TIA collects and holds four broad categories of records (which contain personal data):<br>
               (a) Licensing records – These contain information collected in connection with application for, and issue and renewal of, licences and business permits under the Travel Industry Ordinance (Cap. 634) (TIO) and its subsidiary legislation.<br>
               (b) Complaint, inspection, investigation and disciplinary proceedings records – These contain information collected in respect of complaints made to and inspections, investigations and disciplinary actions conducted by TIA in the discharge of its functions under the TIO;<br>
               (c) Personnel records – These contain personal details, curriculum vitae, job particulars, remuneration, performance appraisals and disciplinary matters of job applicants and staff members of TIA and other relevant information of staff members of TIA.<br>
               (d) Other records – These contain administration and operational files, TIA matters files, data provided to TIA by applicants and participants of promotional and training activities organised by TIA and other training bodies, and enquiries from the public.<br>
     
            <h3>Purposes of Collecting Personal Data</h3>
            <p>3. When we collect personal data from individuals, we will provide them with a Personal Information Collection Statement (PICS) on or before the collection in an appropriate format and manner. The PICS will state (among other matters) the purpose of the collection.</p> 
            <p>4. Personal data are collected and kept for the following main purposes:<br>
                (a) Licensing records are kept for considering and processing applications for licences and business permits, and for keeping a register of travel agents, tourist guides and tour escorts and particulars of licensees for public inspection.<br>
                (b) Complaint, inspection, investigation and disciplinary proceedings records are kept for taking action on complaints, preparation for, and conduct of, disciplinary inquiries under the TIO.<br>
                (c) Personnel records are kept for human resource management.<br>
                (d) Other records are kept for office administration, TIA matters, organisation of promotional and training activities, procurement of services and handling enquiries from the public.<br>
                (e) Contact details of data subjects (including but not limited to their addresses, phone numbers, fax numbers and e-mail addresses, etc.) collected by TIA in the course of carrying out its functions pursuant to the TIO are kept for communication and provision of information on matters concerning travel industry practice to the data subjects where appropriate.<br>
                (f)  Generally speaking, the collection and retention of personal data is for the purpose of exercising the powers and functions of TIA pursuant to the TIO and for compliance with all legal and statutory requirements.<br>
    
            <h3>Data Access / Correction Request</h3>
            <p>5. TIA maintains a log book as provided for in section 27 of PDPO.</p>
            <p>6. Request for access to or correction of personal data by data subjects shall be made to TIA and addressed to its Data Protection Officer with the Data Access Request Form (OPS003) prescribed by the Privacy Commissioner for Personal Data.</p> 
